      "content": "If you're feeling the effects of altitude sickness, a quick fix is to drink plenty of fluids, especially water with electrolytes, to stay hydrated. You can also try taking vitamin C, which some people find helpful in alleviating symptoms. For the tingling sensation, a mild pain reliever like ibuprofen can help, but it's not a cure. If you don't see any improvement or if symptoms worsen, it's better to seek medical help. Remember, it's always better to be safe and consult a doctor, even if it seems inconvenient.",
